-- Taiwan’s CPC Seeks Heavy Low-Sulfur Crude for March Delivery
-- B y   W i n n i e   Z h u
-- 2013-01-15T06:31:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-15/taiwan-s-cpc-seeks-heavy-low-sulfur-crude-for-march-delivery.html
CPC Corp.,  Taiwan ’s state-owned oil
company, issued a tender to buy heavy low-sulfur crude for
delivery in March at the port of Kaohsiung, according to a
 statement  on the company’s website.  Bids were to have been submitted by noon local time today
and must remain valid until 7 p.m. tomorrow, according to the
document.  To contact the reporter on this story:
